(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Nairobi - Kenyan police say they have arrested two suspects accused of planning an attack in the capital, Nairobi.Police spokesperson George Kinoti gave to details of the alleged plot.He said in a statement on Tuesday that Abdulafatah Nur Ali was arrested in Nairobi with a fraudulent national identity card and refugee certificate, and that Farah Shaleh Aden was arrested in Garissa.Kenya has seen attacks by Somali extremist group al-Shabaab, which has vowed retribution on the country for sending troops in 2011 to Somalia to fight the militants. Al-Shabaab has been waging an insurgency against Somalia's weak government.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.